# UUID

## Key Rules

- **ALWAYS use UUID v7** for generating new UUIDs
- Use Ramsey's `Uuid` class for generating and handling UUIDs
- Use `Uuid::uuid7()` for all new UUID generation
- Never use other UUID versions (v1, v3, v4, v5, v6)

## Usage

```php
use Ramsey\Uuid\Uuid;

// Generate UUID v7 as string
$id = Uuid::uuid7()->toString();

// Generate UUID v7 as UuidInterface (also acceptable)
$id = Uuid::uuid7();
```

## Dependencies

- `ramsey/uuid` library
